  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Priyansh, I heard you worked on a project today — how did it go?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It went well. We fixed a bug that was causing delays in payments. My team is happy. I am proud of the work. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s great — fixing bugs that affect payments is no small task. What was the trickiest part of it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The trickiest part was figuring out why the error only happened during peak hours. We had to simulate high traffic to catch it. Took us a few hours, but finally we did it. 😎"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right — simulating high traffic sounds like the key move. What tools did you use for that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We used a tool called JMeter. It helps create a lot of fake requests at once. Also, we checked the logs carefully to find where the problem started. It was a good learning experience. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Nice — JMeter is a solid choice for testing under pressure. What did you learn most from this fix?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I learned how important it is to test under real-like conditions. Small issues can become big during peak times. Also, teamwork made it easier — we all had different ideas, but working together helped. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — real like testing and teamwork are both huge wins. What’s next on your project list?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next, we are adding a new feature for faster user verification. It involves integrating with a third-party API. I need to make sure the data flows correctly and securely. Should be interesting! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Adding a new feature and integrating APIs — that sounds like a big responsibility. What’s your strategy for handling the data flow?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We are making a detailed plan first — like, mapping each input and output. Also, we will do small tests often so we can catch issues early. I will also consult with our security team to ensure everything is safe. It's a bit challenging, but I am excited. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Right — mapping inputs and outputs is smart, and testing early keeps things smooth. How are you handling the API documentation?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The API docs are a bit complex, so I’m going through them step by step. I also asked the API provider for a sample setup — that helps a lot. But honestly, the biggest challenge is making sure the data stays secure during the transfer. Need to be extra careful. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're right — security during data transfer is a big deal. How are you planning to handle encryption?"
    }
  ],
